        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <title>PRODUCTION AND SERVICE LOWER THRUST MAIN BEARING</title>
                <para>A new lower thrust main bearing (#7 position only) was released for production and service with
                    the introduction of the Model Year 2000 engines. The bearing was modified by removing the locking
                    tab as depicted by the illustration
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f01120701" appearance="icon">Lower Thrust Main Bearing and Main Bearing Cap
                        <xref refid="f01120701"/>.
                    </hotlnk>
                </para>
                <figure id="f01120701" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/a0701.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="184px" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Lower Thrust Main Bearing and Main Bearing Cap</caption>
                </figure>
                <para>The modified production and service bearing now affords service technicians the opportunity to
                    install and orient the lower thrust bearing in either direction. The modified bearing is
                    interchangeable with engines released before the Model Year 2000 engines. Model Year 2000 engines
                    are identified by serial number 1194039 and above.
                </para>
                <para>The recommended service procedures for the main bearings and main bearing caps can be found in
                    Service Manual EGES-210.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
